  "diary": "Monday started early and steady—home espresso first, then the drive to Kirkland through clear morning light. The shop was buzzing; I trained Marcus on the new pour-over technique and we got through the lunch rush without any real hiccups. I noticed the bars downtown were already packed by mid-morning with the World Cup match, but that wasn't my scene today.\n\nAfter my shift, I grabbed lunch at home and then spent a couple hours walking around Bellevue with my camera. Found this interesting alley behind the old storefronts with beautiful afternoon shadows—definitely coming back for a proper shoot. QFC was mercifully quiet. Made a simple dinner, played chess with Erin online, and just let the day settle. Organized my camera gear while reading. Felt good to move slowly after being on my feet all morning.",
  "thought_process": "I was planning to take the Light Rail downtown but remembered the maintenance closure, so driving made sense. The World Cup buzz didn't really pull at me—I'm not big on sports crowds—though I noticed how the city energy shifted around it. My mood stayed even and grounded. I chose the photography walk because I've been wanting to scout that neighborhood, and the weather was perfect for it. The chess call with Erin was exactly what I needed after a morning of training and customer interaction; something low-key and connected. By evening I was genuinely tired but satisfied, so I kept things simple with skincare and reading. Nothing dramatic, just a solid day of work and small pleasures.",
